  "description": [
    "FRANK LY SPEAKING 4 r Civil rights for war 6 THE Negro question could decide the 1948 presiden tial election The issue of war or peace o i imperialism or in dependence of a world con trolled by Wall Street or sov ereignity of sister nations can not be separated from Amer icas treatment of her 14000 000 Negro citizens Clarifying these matters is a major job for Wallace supporters I am confident that Presi dent Trumans 10 point civil rights program is not merely bait to lure the Negro vote but is strategy aimed at preparing the way for a possible World War 111 Lets face the fact that fed eral officials know it will not be easy to get Negro Support for a war with Russia The news has gotten around that the Soviet Union has no color line that it is a land without jim crow or lynching Because rtf resentment against our own color preju dice there was opposition among many Negroes to fight ing Hitler despite Nazi racism Winning Negro participation in a conflict with Russia might be so difficult as to stymie the whole adventure THIS was the basis of a su persecret document"
  ],
